Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways then chopped widthways into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @rosemary{1/2}(leaves picked and finely chopped, stalks discarded).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the chopped onion and carrot, cook stirring frequently until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @sliced mushrooms{120} and cook until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once everything has cooked down, add half of the garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Once the garlic has cooked, add the @Vivera Plant Mince{220}, @red wine stock paste{28} and @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}(finely chopped) and @water{150%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir well to combine and simmer without a lid until thickened, ~{15-20%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a bit thick.

Meanwhile, bring a saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. When boiling, add the @spaghetti{200}. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{} pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Whilst everything cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a small #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, add the rosemary and the remaining garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{10} and cook stirring frequently until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once everything is cooked, add the spaghetti to the bolognese and stir to combine. Reheat if necessary. Share the spaghetti bolognese between your bowls and sprinkle the crumb on top. Enjoy!